    {
      "front": "find a healthy balance",
      "meaning": "在坐與站之間取得健康平衡",
      "examples": [
        {
          "en": "The best approach may be to find a healthy balance between sitting and standing.",
          "zh": "最佳方法可能是在坐與站之間取得健康平衡。"
        },
        {
          "en": "To find a healthy balance means to choose a mix that supports health without going too far in one direction.",
          "zh": "取得健康平衡，是選擇一種有助健康、又不偏向某一極端的組合。"
        },
        {
          "en": "Students can find a healthy balance by sitting for focused work and standing during short tasks.",
          "zh": "學生可以在需要專注時坐着，在短任務中站立，從而取得健康平衡。"
        },
        {
          "en": "A healthy routine includes sitting, standing, walking, stretching, and rest.",
          "zh": "健康日常習慣包括坐着、站立、步行、伸展和休息。"
        },
        {
          "en": "Finding a healthy balance is better than replacing one extreme habit with another.",
          "zh": "取得健康平衡，比用另一個極端習慣取代原本的極端習慣更好。"
        }
      ],
      "source": "2015 - 9.2 - Standing desks.pdf",
      "sourcePage": 10
    }
